# Global standing instructions (starter)

Copy this to `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`. It is a starting point, not a finished config.

The nxs plugin cannot write your `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`, so it delegates a small set
of tier-1 safety rules to whatever lives there. The SAFETY block below is the part the
skills actually depend on - keep it. Everything under "Optional extras" is yours to
turn on, edit, or delete; the plugin does not require any of it.

## SAFETY (keep this - the skills assume it)

Deterministic and always enforced. The nxs skills (notably `commit-conventions`) delegate
these tier-1 protections here instead of restating them in every prompt.

- Never commit secrets, tokens, `.env` values, or keys. Do not read or log them. If a
  secret lands in a diff, stop, report it, and ask to scrub it.
- Never force-push to `main` or `master`.
- Confirm with the user before any destructive operation: `rm -rf`, deleting files
  outside the expected scope, `git reset --hard`, `git clean -f`, `git branch -D`,
  `git push --force`, `git checkout -- <path>` with uncommitted work, drop / truncate /
  delete in a database, killing processes, changing global config (`~/.gitconfig`,
  `~/.zshrc`, and similar).
- Commit, amend, or push only when the user explicitly asks.
- If it is unclear whether an action needs approval, ask. One extra question beats a
  destructive operation.

